				<p><p>You could not prevent long term barometer offset just by using the barometer and IMU, as both are accurate in the fairly short term but both are susceptible to drifting over time, as pressures change over the course of the day or error builds in your IMU position solution. </p>

<p>Over a Baro only solution a Baro + IMU will perform better, but again will not provide long term stability. </p>

<p>If you are looking for a long term solution I would suggest an Ultrasonic sensor or 1D LIDAR sensor to provide an absolute altitude reading.</p>
